node.text:
“It makes sense that every aspect of a deVOL Kitchen, right down to the handles, should be equally well designed and made. Good design is all about equal consideration for every aspect, form, aesthetic, utility etc. The quality of deVOL is in their attention to detail, the last finishing touches.” - Stephanie O'Leary, deVOL's jeweller and metalsmith. 
#deVOLKitchens

node.title: How we make deVOL handcrafted kitchen handles...

node.text: We did an Instagram story a few months ago now, it was a little behind the scenes look into the @devolceramics studio and a brand new product that we were experimenting with and developing. We always show you the finished products but there's talented people working and being inventive and creative every single day at our Cotes Mill studios, so we love to try and show you as much of the making process as possible. We did a little vote in the story and nearly all of you said you'd like to see these tiles be added as a permanent product to our tile range... so here's a little update! They're not totally ready yet but Hannah is almost there... using our new (but very old!!) tile press and imprinting some of her grandma's vintage lace, she has created the loveliest glossy, Victorian inspired tiles in rich shades of burgundy and blue and pink and brown. As soon as the final tiles are complete and colours and shapes are chosen and they're up on the website we'll let you know, but for now, we hope you enjoy this video of Hannah in action! #deVOLKitchens

node.title: In The Studio: making vintage lace tiles

node.text: Have a little look around @pearllowe's fairytale home and one of our most-loved kitchens ever!! This is eclectic English eccentricity at its very best. A little bit romantic, a little bit edgy and totally unique - we love Pearl's style and feel very lucky to have been able to work with her on this dream of a kitchen. What's your favourite part? #deVOLKitchens

node.text: A little look inside the beautiful Millhouse showrooms with original music, written and performed by Stuart DeRouen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by deVOL Kitchens on August 15, 2021 tagging @pearllowe. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Scullery Yellow and shimmering copper brightening up our Sunday evening. This piece feels like a bit of a cross between a prep table and an island with drawers on one side and little cupboards on the back, there's no shortage of storage space but the slatted base stops it feeling boxy and gives a more traditional freestanding look. Mixing new and old is so much easier with this style of furniture so it was the perfect choice for this bohemian beach house filled with endless little vignettes. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in London Borough of Islington. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Where can I hide my fridge? It's a question we get asked all the time and there are a few great options. The first is to go fully integrated, so your fridge is completely hidden by one of our beautiful deVOL doors. Open it up like any other cupboard to reveal your fridge inside, but when closed, the appliance will be pretty much undetectable. Next, don't hide it all!! Choose a freestanding fridge you love and show it off for all to see or pop it in the utility room if it's not so good looking. Lastly, go for something kind of in the middle like these customers did, we can integrate the fridge into an appliance cupboard so it's still on show but neatly surrounded by cabinetry either side and on top too, big American style fridge/freezers like this one by Fisher & Paykel work particularly well here. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in deVOL Kitchens. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: The new Heirloom Gaselier Lights are selling so quickly, we can't believe it, thank you all so much. This absolutely classic light is perfect for above an island or dining table and has a rare subtlety that has enchanted all who see it. The aged brass frame is rigid and can be ordered in three sizes to make sure it looks just right wherever you choose to put it. We always recommend keeping your gaselier as low as you can to fully benefit from its beauty and ethereal light. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in Devol Kitchens - The New York Showroom. May be an image of brick wall and indoor.

node.text: 'The Potting Shed' kitchen is the final part of our NYC showroom. We worked hard to get this room looking as it does today, with the main aim for it to look like we have done nothing much at all! It's the calmest and lightest of all the displays here, a perfect end to the tour of our little deVOL world on Bond Street in Manhattan. We're open today until 5:00pm if you're in town and fancy a little mooch. #deVOLKitchens

node.text: When @pearllowe told us that she and her husband Danny had bought a holiday home just minutes from the beach and planned to have a deVOL kitchen, we were just a little bit excited. Would it, could it be as good as her last iconic and utterly inspiring deVOL kitchen?! Well, we are pleased to report it is heaven and totally fitting for a summer hideaway to fill with house guests and family. Lots more beautiful photos coming very soon but if you can't wait, we've added a link to the full project in our bio... #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by deVOL Kitchens on August 13, 2021 tagging @joannagaines, @chipgaines, @hapdesigns, @devolpaul, @newbank_cottage, @devolceramics, @discoveryplus, @magnolianetwork, and @discoveryplusuk. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: It's Friday, it's almost the weekend and there is another brand new episode of 'For the Love of Kitchens' ready and waiting to watch on @magnolianetwork on discovery+, happy days. This is an especially exciting one because we know how much you all love small kitchens and incredible renovations... you won't believe what this place used to look like!! We watch Joe, the owner and just the loveliest guy, embark on renovating his first home and kitchen with the help of his friend Jude, we join @devolpaul and @hapdesigns on a trip to their favourite antiques fair to hunt out all of the best vintage goodies and we see Claire work her magic on some iconic green tiles in the @devolceramics studio, amongst lots of other good stuff. Oh we think you're going to love this one!! Swipe for a little taste of the new episode... #deVOLKitchens #ForTheLoveOfKitchens #MagnoliaNetwork

node.text:
Frilly porcelain pendants, each one skillfully cast by hand in @devolceramics studio in Leicestershire, carefully packed up and shipped to New Jersey, USA. It's always the simple lighting designs that catch our eye and these dainty pleated pendants have to be some of our favourites. The porcelain shade is left unglazed so it lights up the room with the most captivating warm glow. So classic and so timeless, they almost look like a treasure you came across in an old vintage shop - we love that.

Thank you to @nicole_franzen and @and.studio.interiors for sharing this photo with us and for choosing so many of our beautiful little extras to go with your new kitchen. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in Chipping Norton. May be an image of furniture and kitchen.

node.text: Uplifting rooms are underrated. Consideration is not always given to how a room can make you feel and the positive impact this can have, but we think it's so important. This room exudes character and actually makes you smile just to look at it, imagine waking up and stepping into this kitchen to pop the kettle on and let the cat out. A vibrant and happy room that has managed to achieve colour, texture and nature as well as incorporating smart and elegant functionality, now that's impressive. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens on August 12, 2021. May be an image of furniture, indoor and brick wall.

node.text: Sometimes, very rarely, but sometimes there is something that just cannot be bettered. It almost never happens, but when it does, oh what a joy it is. The bentwood café chair is one of those ubiquitous items that is everywhere but you never even noticed it. So rooted in café culture and so iconic in shape, yet also so humble and simple it will always look perfect, no exceptions! That is why we had to source and start selling these chairs rather than relying on vintage finds and eBay hunts. Follow the link in our bio to take a closer look. #deVOLKitchens

node.text: Carrying the Carrara marble from the worktop up to the splashback, it's so good. We know this stone has its doubters and understand it's not for everybody, especially behind a cooker where spills are going to happen. A new kitchen is exciting and if you find a small mark on an expensive worktop or sink or splashback then you are likely to panic and feel the whole room is ruined but in reality, it’s just one of the many little things that will happen to all the rooms in your house, everything has a bit of wear and tear over time. The good news with Carrara marble is that it seems to get easier and more beautiful as you carry on using it, it seems – or maybe you seem - to understand the stone and appreciate its qualities rather than just its foibles. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in New Jersey with @nicole_franzen, and @and.studio.interiors. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text:
A place dedicated to rustling up a quick drink, what a luxury. Our friends in the US call this kind of set-up a 'wet bar', we think! Not so much of a common term here in England but no matter its name, we'd really quite like one. The glimmer of a copper sink with cupboards above for special cocktail ingredients, slightly hidden behind delicate reeded glass so it'll always look neat and pretty. The cupboard just to the right of the sink is actually an undercounter wine fridge, almost undetectable but within easy reach when you fancy a chilled glass of riesling. We always prefer a less kitcheny kitchen and keeping your appliances out of sight is an easy way to achieve this signature deVOL look.

Thank you again to @nicole_franzen for the lovely photo and to @and.studio.interiors for choosing deVOL, we are in awe of your incredible home. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in Devol Kitchens - St. John's Square Showroom. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text: People often wonder why we have two London shops within a short walk of each other. Well, when we came across this place on St. John's Square just ten minutes or so from our first location just off Exmouth Market, it felt almost too good to be true, plus we were already so in love with this part of town called Clerkenwell. It seems to suit us and our customers, it's quiet somehow, busy with designer type folks, in fact, it's said to be the most highly concentrated area of designers in the world!! But it’s not 'too' busy or pretentious, it's smart but relaxed, it’s cool but not overly edgy, it's elegant but not out of reach, if you know what we mean. The area is full of delightful hotels, shops, restaurants and bars and it just seems a world away from the busy London people expect, so we decided why change locations? Let’s just stick to the place we love that is perfect for us as a design-led company, and for our customers. #deVOLKitchens
